1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Ever wondered why your body shuts down during dreams?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:07,200
It's called REM atonia; your brain inhibits most muscles.

3
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:10,800
This protective mechanism prevents you from acting out dreams.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:14,800
However, misfires can lead to sleep paralysis, an eerie experience.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,400
Preliminary research suggests this might be a brain glitch.

6
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:21,200
Want to dive deeper into sleep science?

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,800
Hit like and subscribe!
